    "body": "https://github.com/google-deepmind/alphaevolve_repository_of_problems/blob/main/problems/52.html#L219\n\nAccording to the construction mentioned in the article, which is \"n = 7 mod 25\", the problem should actually ask about \n\n> the largest cardinality of a subset $A$ of $\\\\{1,\\\\dots,N\\\\}$ with the property that $ab+1$ is **NOT** square-free for all $a,b \\\\in A$\n\n(since 7^2+1 = 0 mod 25, therefore all ab+1 are not square-free, as opposed to being square-free like in the current version of the problem description).\n\nSo, there seems to be a typo. In a private email conversation, @teorth confirmed that this is indeed a typo introduced during the writing of the paper.",
